1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Nf3 ({This is a very common Club Player move. White isn't trying to beat you, they're just getting out their knights and bishops. Now, we have to be a little careful here as Nbd7 , our usual move, blocks in our light-squared c8 bishop. So,} 6. Bc4 {would create an awkward moment where we can't play our usual move inviting doubled pawns.}) 6... Bd6 ({Now Bc4} 6... Be6 {is just a transposition to the Queen Trade Bc4 variation, covered earlier.}) 7. Ng5 {White attacks the f7 pawn. This is a very simple threat with a very simple reply. The position after Ng5 is technically still equal but Black wins a lot here even when they don't know the opening moves. It was tempting for me to not even include it and just have players go with their gut but I don't know everyone's 'gut' so I'll spell it out but keep it short.} Ke7 (7... Rf8 {also works equally well, but we can daydream about getting the Bc4 line a tempo up--there we wanted the king on e7 anyway. We no longer have to worry about Bg5 because the knight is occupying that square and when we kick it with h6 , we will eliminate that Bg5 option permanently.}) 8. Bc4 {Consistent. If not for this move, we will play h6 , a move we often want to play anyway and blocks all the scarier Bg5 lines, and the knight move will have done nothing. White hopes we will blindly surrender our bishop to the knight and play 8. ... Be6 here. However, we should not be so obliging.  Be6 will only be a good move once the knight has retreated.} Rf8 ({Here, White's moves have fizzled out. For example, if White plays O-O , we will play} 8... h6 9. Nf3 Be6 10. Bxe6 fxe6 {and enter a hyper accelerated version of the Bc4 lines, where we got Ke7 and h6 in and opened up a file for our rook! We can then pawn storm the kingside.}) ({If they play} 8... Nd5 {the game will be a bit more original but very intuitive. We will respond} 9. Nxd5+ {Bxd5 or else the bishop is blocked in and the pawn is weak f6 and we are very solid and on the way to pawn storming.  c6 will come for free as it hits the white bishop and g5 is possible, too.}) *

