 rook, a precarious c3 knight, and an attacked queen. From here on out, you'll have to calculate as White has many moves though they will lose at least a piece every time. Don't get me wrong, all of those many moves lose, but memorization is no longer in order, just try to get to this position and calculate to victory.} ({Best moves for both sides goes Qe3 Ng4 Qd3} 20... Qb4 21. Raa1 Nxc3 {when Black has taken a piece and their attack continues.}) *

