1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. f4 {White weeps that they didn't get the Austrian Attack against the Pirc and tries to play it against the Philidor. White is trying to bully us into losing our center. They will have their way but to misquote the Princess Bride: You keep urging us to take on d4 , I do not think it means, what you think it means.' I don't have any super GM's playing this move, a telling sign given that super GM battles take place in the Philidor all the time. The highest rated player to play it is Julian Hodgson at 2640 (which is admittedly close to, if not already a, super GM). But the one game in it involved him losing to someone 240 points lower than him, so even that isn't the biggest sell from the White point of view. On the other hand, if Black takes the wrong pawn, White is suddenly winning a lot--65% to Black's 25% in Master play--so this is a dangerous position you can't merely intuit, and unlike our normal ones--hence the three chapters. Once you know the early moves though, you should smile every time White plays this way.} exd4 5. Qxd4 {This is a perfect example of a good reason to take on d4 : the move f4 doesn't develop a piece so White will lag behind in development and doubly so because Nc6 will hit their queen. The move f4 also means they can't play f3 to defend e4 when the going gets tough. Finally, the extra tempos mean we can develop the bishop to the long diagonal right away without worrying about Bc4  Nf3 - g5 stuff (it will be way too slow for White).} Nc6 6. Qe3 ({A sensible retreat.} 6. Qd3 {would have given Black Nb4 options and blocked in the bishop.}) 6... g6 {Because e4 is weak, Be7 may block our rook from attacking it and every tempo matters. Also, from g7 , our bishop will light up the long diagonal.} 7. Bd2 {Trying to castle queenside.} Bg7 8. O-O-O O-O {Now safe, we can work on attacking the center and White's king.} 9. Nf3 Re8 {A good game will take place. We have some pressure on the e-file and a6  b5 pawnstorm ideas. In fact, only Bc4 is equal for White and all other moves give Black a tiny advantage according to Stockfish 14. We can play Bf5 and d5 because of the pins on the e-file.} *

