 Bc5 11. Nh3 {And now Qh4 + and Nd4 are both winning. White has too many weaknesses.} Nd4 {The queen doesn't have many safe places to go that aren't horribly passive. Therefore, they should take the d5 pawn.} 12. Qxd5 Qh4+ {g3 isn't possible because of the vulnerable knight... Qxh3 .} 13. Kd2 {The best square. And not a pretty one.} Bb6 {Protecting the bishop and preparing Bc6 , O-O-O and more fun.} 14. Ng5 Qf2+ ({And now after} 14... Ne2 {the moves O-O-O , Qe3 , and Be6 are all good for Black (like a rook up good). White's king is on d2 and they are hurting. The eval bar sits around -5 due to Black's attack so you can choose whichever of those three finishers you like best.}) *

