[PlyCount "28"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4 {Please see this informational, if you haven't already checked it out, for what this move is all about and why I think we should respond as follows.} g6 6. g5 Nh5 7. Bh3 {This is a popular move at Master level play, but not so much club player level. This would be a low priority line to study against, say, a 1500 rated player. Whenever the bishop goes to h3 , we need to start thinking about moving our knight. The bishop trade would normally be just good bishop versus bad bishop in our opponent's favor but the move g4 has really weakened the light squares making it a bit more complicated.} exd4 {In expectation of a bishop trade, we counterattack in the center and make way for a strong dark-squared bishop.} 8. Qxd4 Bg7 {Here e5 was played in an 1100 game on Lichess and White fell apart because, well, it's losing a pawn. But actually White is in trouble no matter what. Let's follow a natural line to see why.} 9. Qe3 O-O 10. Bd2 {Technically b5 here is best but we don't need to get into daring pawn sacrifices to improve our advantage from -1.7 to -2.0 in more obscure lines. Black can play naturally here with c6 or f5 . Let's check out c6 as it's the most natural.} c6 11. O-O-O b5 {The attack on the queenside is terrifying and White's attack looks stalled.} 12. Kb1 Re8 {Why not eye the queen? We are now at a point where we can reflect on the position. Black has a great attack and White can barely move on the kingside. The engine suggests Bc1 here, but I think Bg4 is the more human move, trying to get something going on the kingside. If White plays the right move here (Bc1 then maybe b4 by Black) they are at a clear disadvantage but can perhaps hold with good play.} 13. Bg4 b4 14. Ne2 d5 {This is what happens if White delays. Not only does Black have a great wing attack, but the center play is quite powerful. e4 is hanging, the bishop on g7 is a monster, the d7 knight has choice ways to leap into action and Black is crushing in this position with a winning advantage.} *

