1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4 {Please see this informational, if you haven't already checked it out, for what this move is all about and why I think we should respond as follows.} g6 6. g5 Nh5 7. Bh3 {This is a popular move at Master level play, but not so much club player level. This would be a low priority line to study against, say, a 1500 rated player. Whenever the bishop goes to h3 , we need to start thinking about moving our knight. The bishop trade would normally be just good bishop versus bad bishop in our opponent's favor but the move g4 has really weakened the light squares making it a bit more complicated.} exd4 {In expectation of a bishop trade, we counterattack in the center and make way for a strong dark-squared bishop.} 8. Nxd4 {Definitely the best move and the one chosen by Aronian vs. Vachier Lagrave in a game in 2014. No need to give Black a tempo on the queen. Vachier Lagrave played h6 here and drew the game despite some opening troubles. I analyzed it and found it was possibly equalizing in a very weird position where Black had to play the counter-intuitive and seemingly anti-positional c5 , but the play was irrational and hard to memorize. The simplest option here is to just neutralize the bishop on h3 .} Nb6 9. Bg2 {Trading bishops with Bxc8  Nxc8 will simplify things and lead to equality as well.} Bg7 {We're in unexplored territory here. Black should be able to achieve d5 at some point. If they can activate their knight, they will be in a good place. This can be achieved by h6 and if White plays h4 , their king will feel a breeze on the kingside and the g5 pawn will be a bit weak.... so because we need the rook to support that move, we shouldn't rush to castle.} 10. O-O h6 11. gxh6 Bxh6 12. f4 Bd7 {White has played some very brilliant moves in an unknown position and has a slight edge. That said, it's only slight and Black's position is very playable. We will probably castle kingside when we feel like it or put our king on f8 , enjoying the h-file rook for now, and put pressure on the dark squares with Qh4 . It's very imbalanced and should be a good game!} *

