1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 {This looks like it can transpose to f3 later but it's not possible for White to get there with Nc3 as the third move.} e5 ({Now} 3... d5 {c6 or} 4. exd5 {Be7 would be a line handled elsewhere--'Tension Variation Club Player Mainline.' The second of those could transpose to an f3 line but not one in which White can play c4 , which is the most dangerous line.}) 4. f3 {White plans a possible d5 but no knight is guarding d4 , so...} exd4 5. Qxd4 Nc6 {And Black has gained several tempos and will fianchetto the bishop making it scary for White to castle queenside.} *

