1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Be3 {This, too, doesn't get White into their setup because we can chase the bishop before they've played f3 .} Ng4 5. Bc1 {No other move effectively saved the bishop as Bd2 was dropping the pawn on d4 . Black can now play Nf6 and ask White to try again or can play for a win with...} exd4 6. Qxd4 Nc6 {With an interesting game ahead of us; Black can even play f5 with the knight on g4 if they want to!} *

