ened anyway.} fxe3 11. Qxe3 {We are delighted at trading our bad bishop for White's bishop, AND doubling their h pawns. We are immediately up a pawn and have a nice outpost for the knight.} Qxh4+ {And the f-file pressure along with the trade of bishops give Black a sizeable edge.} 12. Qf2 Qe7 {With Na6  Bd7 or Bg4 to follow and Black will play knights into all the dark outposts! Black stands better.} *

