1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Rg1 {This move just transposes. I mentioned this in an informational but putting it here so people can find it more easily. This requires care if you accept the gambit, but we don't so have much less stress trying to innovate here.} c6 6. g4 g6 {This transposes to the Shirov Gambit line. You can find that variation by clicking here. (Or perhaps they will push an early g5 with play similar to the chapters with White playing a suboptimal rook move, as the rook doesn't attack much on the g-file.)} *

