1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 (5. Rg1 {This move just transposes.} c6 6. g4 g6 {This transposes to the Shirov Gambit line. You can find that variation by clicking here.}) 5... Be7 6. Ng5 O-O 7. Bxf7+ Rxf7 8. Ne6 Qe8 9. Nxc7 Qd8 10. Nxa8 b5 11. O-O Bb7 12. Nxb5 Bxa8 13. Nxa7 Qb8 14. Be3 {This line was given in the course here and I stand by 14... Bxe4 because of its simplicity: just take back one of the pawns. The engines think Black is fine and in human play, I'd give Black an edge. However, there was a request for even more--you can get objectively more if you want to lean into the crazy--and if you know White plays this, you might want to opt for this much more complicated line to maximize your winning chances. So here's a Movetrainer Alternative for Masters or those who know White will play this. Buckle your seatbelts, this isn't for the faint of heart...} exd4 ({Now on Qxd4} 14... Ng4 {Qc3 Nxe3 Qxe3 Nc5 , Black takes out the bishop and gives Black good play with a clear advantage according to the engine so instead best is...}) 15. Bxd4 Nxe4 {Black recaptures the pawn which opens up their bishop.} 16. Qe2 {Best, connecting the rooks. Against most other moves, we would respond the same way.} Ne5 {The only move that preserves Black's advantage. Black must play actively with all of their pieces. Next up is Qf8 and kingside attacks or Bb7 and Qa8 .} 17. f3 {White tries to push back Black's pieces.} Ng5 ({Again, the best move by a lot: White is close to equalizing with an inaccuracy. As I said, this line is tricky. The goal is to sacrifice the knight, and White's king will not survive the onslaught of pieces. For example, Qe3} 17... Nxf3+ 18. Rxf3 {Bxf3 Rf1 is a computer line showing how crazy things are... and Black is doing amazing there.}) 18. Qb5 ({Best. It looks like White has a fork but it's a trainwreck:} 18. f4 Nh3+ 19. gxh3 Qb7 {with unstoppable threats on the long diagonal.}) 18... Bb7 {Black refuses the trade of queens and prepares more assaults on the long diagonal with bishop sacrifice threats after the queen arrives on a8 , and a rerouting of the knight. Black stands objectively better, around -.80 according to my Stockfish engine--though it is an exciting and chaotic game ahead.} *

